WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:19.000
Cheedeb presents, Zorro, by Johnston McCully.

00:31.000 --> 00:39.000
This story takes place in Spanish, California during the first part of the 1800s.

00:39.000 --> 00:44.000
The word Zorro means Fox in Spanish.

00:44.000 --> 00:51.000
The story of Zorro is an old legend from Spanish, California.

00:52.000 --> 00:57.000
Chapter 1. A Stormy Night

00:57.000 --> 01:03.000
Reina de Los Angeles is a Spanish village in Southern California.

01:03.000 --> 01:10.000
In the village, there is a military procedure with Spanish soldiers and their horses.

01:10.000 --> 01:15.000
There is also a Spanish church called a mission.

01:15.000 --> 01:18.000
The Spanish friars live here.

01:18.000 --> 01:26.000
All around the village, there are big homes with patios.

01:26.000 --> 01:36.000
Tonight, there is a terrible storm, and it is raining.

01:36.000 --> 01:41.000
Inside the village tavern, there are soldiers and other men.

01:41.000 --> 01:45.000
They are eating and drinking.

01:45.000 --> 01:49.000
Sergeant Pedro Gonzalez is at the tavern.

01:49.000 --> 01:53.000
He is a big, strong man.

01:53.000 --> 01:55.000
What a horrible night.

01:55.000 --> 01:58.000
It always rains in February.

01:58.000 --> 02:01.000
Where is Zorro on this stormy night?

02:01.000 --> 02:03.000
Asks one soldier.

02:03.000 --> 02:06.000
Zorro, don't say that name.

02:06.000 --> 02:09.000
He is abandoned and a criminal.

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
Says Sergeant Gonzalez.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.000
He is the terror of Southern California.

02:15.000 --> 02:17.000
Says another soldier.

02:17.000 --> 02:21.000
People say that he takes from the rich and gives to the poor.

02:21.000 --> 02:25.000
He is a friend of the natives and the friars.

02:25.000 --> 02:29.000
He punishes dishonest people, says an old man.

02:29.000 --> 02:33.000
Huh, Zorro is a big mystery.

02:33.000 --> 02:36.000
Who is he? Where is he from?

02:36.000 --> 02:40.000
He wears a black mask and no one can see his face.

02:40.000 --> 02:45.000
He travels on the El Camino Real on his fast horse.

02:45.000 --> 02:48.000
He is very good with his sword.

02:48.000 --> 02:49.000
Says the Sergeant.

02:49.000 --> 02:52.000
Yes, and he leaves his mark.

02:52.000 --> 02:54.000
The Z, everywhere.

02:54.000 --> 02:57.000
Says the old man.

02:57.000 --> 02:59.000
No one can stop him.

02:59.000 --> 03:04.000
The governor of California offers a big reward for the capture of Zorro.

03:04.000 --> 03:08.000
Says one soldier.

03:08.000 --> 03:11.000
At that moment, a man enters the tavern.

03:11.000 --> 03:13.000
He is young and handsome.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
He has black hair and dark eyes.

03:16.000 --> 03:18.000
He has fine clothes.

03:18.000 --> 03:22.000
Don Diego Vega, my friend.

03:22.000 --> 03:24.000
Says Sergeant Gonzalez.

03:24.000 --> 03:26.000
Your clothes are wet.

03:26.000 --> 03:30.000
Why are you out on this rainy night?

03:30.000 --> 03:32.000
Don Diego smiles and says,

03:32.000 --> 03:36.000
I am going home, but I am cold and wet.

03:36.000 --> 03:39.000
I want something to drink.

03:39.000 --> 03:41.000
Come and stand near the fire.

03:41.000 --> 03:42.000
Says the Sergeant.

03:42.000 --> 03:45.000
Here is a glass of wine.

03:45.000 --> 03:46.000
Thank you, my friend.

03:46.000 --> 03:48.000
Says Don Diego.

03:48.000 --> 03:50.000
We are talking about Zorro.

03:50.000 --> 03:54.000
Everyone is scared of him, but I am not.

03:54.000 --> 03:57.000
I am ready to fight Zorro and win.

03:57.000 --> 03:59.000
I am a champion with the sword.

03:59.000 --> 04:01.000
What do you think, Don Diego?

04:01.000 --> 04:03.000
Ask the Sergeant.

04:03.000 --> 04:07.000
Everyone talks about this mysterious man with a mask.

04:07.000 --> 04:09.000
Many people say good things about him.

04:09.000 --> 04:11.000
Says Don Diego.

04:11.000 --> 04:14.000
I want to fight him and capture him.

04:14.000 --> 04:16.000
I want the big reward.

04:16.000 --> 04:18.000
Says Sergeant Gonzalez.

04:18.000 --> 04:19.000
No, no.

04:19.000 --> 04:21.000
Don't talk about fighting.

04:21.000 --> 04:23.000
I hate fighting and I hate violence.

04:23.000 --> 04:25.000
I think Zorro is sincere.

04:25.000 --> 04:28.000
He punishes only bad people.

04:28.000 --> 04:32.000
He protects the poor, the natives and the friars.

04:32.000 --> 04:34.000
Let Zorro do his work.

04:34.000 --> 04:36.000
Says Don Diego.

04:36.000 --> 04:38.000
You are a kind man.

04:38.000 --> 04:40.000
You like music and poetry.

04:40.000 --> 04:43.000
You don't understand, my friend.

04:43.000 --> 04:45.000
You are rich and noble.

04:45.000 --> 04:47.000
Says the Sergeant.

04:47.000 --> 04:49.000
Don Diego smiles and says,

04:49.000 --> 04:52.000
It's 6 p.m. I must return to my hacienda.

04:52.000 --> 04:54.000
Good night, everyone.

04:54.000 --> 04:59.000
He opens the tavern door and goes out into the rain.

05:03.000 --> 05:08.000
Chapter 2, a surprise visit.

05:08.000 --> 05:13.000
At 7 p.m. the door of the tavern opens.

05:13.000 --> 05:19.000
Sergeant Gonzalez and the other soldiers are standing near the fire.

05:19.000 --> 05:25.000
They are talking about Don Diego Vega and his rich family.

05:25.000 --> 05:29.000
They turn around and see a man.

05:29.000 --> 05:32.000
He is dressed in black.

05:32.000 --> 05:36.000
He has a black mask and a black sombrero.

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
It is Zorro.

05:38.000 --> 05:39.000
Good evening.

05:39.000 --> 05:41.000
My name is Zorro.

05:41.000 --> 05:43.000
Says the masked man.

05:43.000 --> 05:48.000
The men in the tavern are very surprised and scared.

05:48.000 --> 05:52.000
Sergeant Gonzalez looks at him carefully and says,

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
What do you want, Bandit?

05:56.000 --> 05:58.000
Zorro laughs loudly.

05:58.000 --> 06:01.000
He looks at Sergeant Gonzalez and says,

06:01.000 --> 06:04.000
I am here to punish you, Sergeant.

06:04.000 --> 06:06.000
What do you mean?

06:06.000 --> 06:08.000
Says the Sergeant.

06:08.000 --> 06:10.000
You beat the poor natives.

06:10.000 --> 06:12.000
I'm a friend of the natives.

06:12.000 --> 06:14.000
I am here to punish you.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
You idiot.

06:16.000 --> 06:18.000
The governor wants you dead or alive.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
Says Sergeant Gonzalez.

06:20.000 --> 06:24.000
He pulls out his sword and wants to fight.

06:24.000 --> 06:28.000
At that moment, Zorro pulls out a pistol.

06:28.000 --> 06:31.000
He watches everyone carefully.

06:31.000 --> 06:35.000
Sergeant Gonzalez looks at the pistol and says,

06:35.000 --> 06:38.000
Courageous men don't use pistols.

06:38.000 --> 06:40.000
They use swords.

06:40.000 --> 06:43.000
Perhaps you are not courageous, Zorro.

06:43.000 --> 06:47.000
This pistol is necessary because you have many friends in this tavern.

06:47.000 --> 06:50.000
Everyone must go near the fire and stay there.

06:50.000 --> 06:51.000
Says Zorro.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.000
Now I have a pistol in my left hand and a sword in my right hand.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
I am ready to punish you.

06:57.000 --> 06:58.000
Fight, Senor!

06:58.000 --> 07:00.000
Says the Sergeant.

07:01.000 --> 07:03.000
They start fighting.

07:03.000 --> 07:07.000
Their swords move quickly and make a lot of noise.

07:07.000 --> 07:10.000
The two men are good fighters.

07:10.000 --> 07:13.000
Zorro is fast and light.

07:13.000 --> 07:16.000
Sergeant Gonzalez is slow and heavy.

07:16.000 --> 07:19.000
Zorro jumps onto a table.

07:19.000 --> 07:21.000
Then he jumps onto a chair.

07:21.000 --> 07:27.000
The fight continues and Sergeant Gonzalez's sword falls onto the floor.

07:27.000 --> 07:29.000
His face is white.

07:29.000 --> 07:31.000
He is scared.

07:31.000 --> 07:34.000
Zorro slaps his face and says,

07:34.000 --> 07:37.000
This is your punishment.

07:37.000 --> 07:43.000
Then he makes a Z on the Sergeant's shirt with his sword.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.000
Zorro runs to the window.

07:45.000 --> 07:48.000
He opens it and says,

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
Good evening, gentlemen.

07:50.000 --> 07:54.000
He jumps out of the window and disappears.

07:57.000 --> 07:59.000
Chapter 3.

07:59.000 --> 08:02.000
The Pulido Hacienda

08:03.000 --> 08:06.000
The next day is warm and sunny.

08:06.000 --> 08:10.000
Don Diego gets on his beautiful horse.

08:10.000 --> 08:15.000
He rides to Don Carlos Pulido's big Hacienda.

08:16.000 --> 08:20.000
Don Carlos is a good friend of Don Diego's family.

08:20.000 --> 08:24.000
Both families are rich and important.

08:24.000 --> 08:27.000
But the governor does not like Don Carlos.

08:27.000 --> 08:30.000
He creates problems for him.

08:30.000 --> 08:33.000
He wants to take Don Carlos's land.

08:33.000 --> 08:36.000
Don Carlos is happy to see his friend.

08:36.000 --> 08:38.000
Good morning, Don Diego.

08:38.000 --> 08:40.000
What a nice surprise.

08:40.000 --> 08:42.000
Come and sit in the patio.

08:42.000 --> 08:43.000
Thank you.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.000
I am here to say something very important.

08:46.000 --> 08:47.000
Says Don Diego.

08:47.000 --> 08:50.000
I am almost 25 years old.

08:50.000 --> 08:53.000
My father wants me to get married and start a family.

08:53.000 --> 08:56.000
I am not interested in marriage.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
I think love and marriage are boring.

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
But I must obey my father.

09:00.000 --> 09:03.000
How old is your daughter Lolita?

09:03.000 --> 09:05.000
Asks Don Diego.

09:05.000 --> 09:08.000
Lolita is 18 years old and she is very beautiful.

09:08.000 --> 09:10.000
Answers Don Carlos.

09:10.000 --> 09:12.000
You have a fine family.

09:12.000 --> 09:15.000
With your permission, I want to marry your daughter.

09:15.000 --> 09:17.000
Says Don Diego.

09:17.000 --> 09:20.000
Don Carlos smiles and is happy.

09:20.000 --> 09:22.000
This is an honor for our family.

09:22.000 --> 09:24.000
You have my permission.

09:24.000 --> 09:26.000
Do you want to see Lolita?

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
I think I must.

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
Answers Don Diego.

09:30.000 --> 09:34.000
Don Carlos calls her and she comes to the patio.

09:34.000 --> 09:39.000
Lolita is a lovely girl with long black hair and dark eyes.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
Good morning, Senorita.

09:41.000 --> 09:43.000
There is something I must tell you.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.000
Says Don Diego smiling.

09:45.000 --> 09:48.000
I want to marry you and your father approves.

09:48.000 --> 09:50.000
Oh, Senor.

09:50.000 --> 09:51.000
Exclaims Lolita.

09:51.000 --> 09:53.000
You want to marry me?

09:53.000 --> 09:57.000
She is surprised and her face is red.

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
Think about it today.

09:59.000 --> 10:02.000
One of my servants can bring me your answer tomorrow.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
But why can't you come tomorrow?

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
Asks Lolita.

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
Oh, your hussy end is far.

10:09.000 --> 10:11.000
I get tired when I ride my horse.

10:11.000 --> 10:14.000
I prefer to stay at home and rest.

10:14.000 --> 10:15.000
What?

10:15.000 --> 10:19.000
You want to marry me and you don't want to visit me?

10:19.000 --> 10:22.000
Is this your idea of love?

10:22.000 --> 10:26.000
I want to marry a strong romantic man.

10:26.000 --> 10:31.000
You are young and rich, but you are not strong or romantic.

10:31.000 --> 10:32.000
Do you have a heart?

10:32.000 --> 10:34.000
Says Lolita.

10:34.000 --> 10:36.000
She is angry.

10:36.000 --> 10:39.000
She runs away and tells her mother.

10:39.000 --> 10:41.000
Donna Catalina says...

10:41.000 --> 10:43.000
You are lucky Lolita.

10:43.000 --> 10:46.000
Don Diego is very rich.

10:46.000 --> 10:49.000
He comes from a noble family.

10:49.000 --> 10:51.000
The governor likes his family.

10:51.000 --> 10:55.000
This is a big opportunity for our family.

10:55.000 --> 10:59.000
In the afternoon, Lolita is alone in the patio.

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
She is thinking about Don Diego.

11:02.000 --> 11:06.000
Suddenly, she hears a noise and turns around.

11:06.000 --> 11:09.000
She sees Zorro standing in front of her.

11:09.000 --> 11:10.000
Zorro.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.000
She whispers.

11:11.000 --> 11:13.000
Don't be afraid, Senorita.

11:13.000 --> 11:16.000
I only punish corrupt people.

11:16.000 --> 11:18.000
I like your father because he is honest.

11:18.000 --> 11:20.000
I'm here to admire your beauty.

11:20.000 --> 11:23.000
What? You must go away.

11:23.000 --> 11:25.000
You are in great danger.

11:25.000 --> 11:27.000
Says Lolita.

11:27.000 --> 11:30.000
You are beautiful and kind, Lolita.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.000
Says Zorro.

11:31.000 --> 11:33.000
You kiss your hand.

11:33.000 --> 11:36.000
Zorro takes her small hand and kisses it.

11:36.000 --> 11:41.000
Lolita looks into his eyes and smiles.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.000
Then she runs into the house.

11:43.000 --> 11:46.000
What a courageous man.

11:46.000 --> 11:49.000
He is a bandit, but I like him.

11:49.000 --> 11:51.000
Lolita thinks.

11:53.000 --> 11:55.000
Spanish California.

11:55.000 --> 11:58.000
Read this page from a Spanish friars diary

11:58.000 --> 12:01.000
and learn about Spanish California.

12:01.000 --> 12:04.000
San Diego de Alcala.

12:04.000 --> 12:07.000
April 22, 1802.

12:07.000 --> 12:10.000
California is a beautiful place.

12:10.000 --> 12:13.000
It is always warm and sunny.

12:13.000 --> 12:17.000
There are flowers and fruit trees everywhere.

12:17.000 --> 12:21.000
I live in the San Diego de Alcala mission.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
Other friars live here too.

12:23.000 --> 12:27.000
San Diego de Alcala is the first Californian mission.

12:27.000 --> 12:31.000
Many Indians live in the village near the mission.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.000
They are friendly.

12:33.000 --> 12:36.000
We teach them many things.

12:36.000 --> 12:39.000
Spanish families live here too.

12:39.000 --> 12:43.000
Some rich families have big haciendas.

12:43.000 --> 12:48.000
The village of San Diego de Alcala is growing quickly.

12:48.000 --> 12:51.000
It is near the Pacific Ocean.

12:51.000 --> 12:56.000
Spanish ships often come and bring things from Spain.

12:56.000 --> 13:00.000
Some villages have military presidios.

13:00.000 --> 13:04.000
Spanish soldiers live in the presidios.

13:04.000 --> 13:09.000
Today, friar Junipero Serra is visiting us.

13:09.000 --> 13:12.000
He is a very important friar.

13:12.000 --> 13:16.000
He travels and builds missions in California.

13:16.000 --> 13:20.000
He wants to build 21 missions.

13:20.000 --> 13:23.000
Some big missions in California are

13:23.000 --> 13:39.000
San Juan Capistrano, Reina de Los Angeles, Santa Barbara, San Luis Obispo, Carmel, San Francisco.

13:39.000 --> 13:44.000
Chapter 4, Captain Ramon.

13:44.000 --> 13:49.000
At 8 p.m., it is dinner time at Don Carlos's home.

13:49.000 --> 13:52.000
The family is sitting at the table.

13:52.000 --> 13:55.000
Someone knocks at the door.

13:55.000 --> 13:58.000
A servant opens it.

13:58.000 --> 14:01.000
And Zorro appears.

14:01.000 --> 14:05.000
Don Carlos, his wife and daughter, stand up.

14:05.000 --> 14:07.000
They are scared.

14:07.000 --> 14:09.000
Good evening, says Zorro.

14:09.000 --> 14:11.000
Don't be scared.

14:11.000 --> 14:13.000
You are an honest man, Don Carlos.

14:13.000 --> 14:16.000
I only want some food and drink.

14:16.000 --> 14:19.000
Zorro goes to Lolita and whispers.

14:19.000 --> 14:22.000
I cannot forget this afternoon in the patio.

14:22.000 --> 14:24.000
You must not come here.

14:24.000 --> 14:25.000
It is dangerous.

14:25.000 --> 14:28.000
Whispers Lolita.

14:28.000 --> 14:32.000
Suddenly, a young Spanish soldier enters the house.

14:32.000 --> 14:34.000
He is Captain Ramon.

14:34.000 --> 14:37.000
He wants to arrest Zorro.

14:37.000 --> 14:40.000
Zorro takes out his sword and they fight.

14:40.000 --> 14:43.000
The two men are good fighters.

14:43.000 --> 14:45.000
I want to arrest you, Zorro!

14:45.000 --> 14:47.000
Says Captain Ramon.

14:47.000 --> 14:49.000
You are a public enemy!

14:49.000 --> 14:52.000
You cannot arrest me, says Zorro.

14:52.000 --> 14:58.000
Zorro injures the Captain's shoulder with his sword.

14:58.000 --> 15:00.000
The Captain falls to the floor.

15:00.000 --> 15:02.000
Please help the Captain.

15:02.000 --> 15:13.000
Zorro says to Don Carlos, then he smiles at Lolita and rides away on his horse.

15:13.000 --> 15:19.000
Don Carlos' wife and daughter look after Captain Ramon's injured shoulder.

15:19.000 --> 15:22.000
The Captain likes beautiful Lolita.

15:22.000 --> 15:25.000
Don Carlos, says the Captain.

15:25.000 --> 15:27.000
I like Lolita very much.

15:27.000 --> 15:32.000
I come from a good family and I am the Governor's friend.

15:32.000 --> 15:36.000
I'm 23 years old and I am the Captain of the Presidio.

15:36.000 --> 15:39.000
May I court Lolita.

15:39.000 --> 15:41.000
First, I must explain something.

15:41.000 --> 15:43.000
Says Don Carlos.

15:43.000 --> 15:47.000
Don Diego Vega wants to court Lolita too.

15:47.000 --> 15:54.000
Lolita must choose her husband herself, but you have my permission to court her.

15:54.000 --> 15:58.000
The next morning, there is a lot of noise at the Presidio.

15:58.000 --> 16:02.000
Don Diego and other men are watching.

16:02.000 --> 16:05.000
There are many soldiers on their horses.

16:05.000 --> 16:10.000
They are listening to Sergeant Gonzales.

16:10.000 --> 16:13.000
Today is an important day.

16:13.000 --> 16:15.000
We must find Zorro.

16:15.000 --> 16:19.000
We must look in every Hacienda and in every home.

16:19.000 --> 16:22.000
Remember the Governor's big reward.

16:22.000 --> 16:24.000
Let's go!

16:24.000 --> 16:29.000
That morning, Don Diego sends a letter to Don Carlos.

16:29.000 --> 16:34.000
My dear friend, Sergeant Gonzales and his soldiers want to arrest Zorro.

16:34.000 --> 16:38.000
It is dangerous for you and your family to stay at your Hacienda.

16:38.000 --> 16:42.000
Please come to my home in Reina de Los Angeles.

16:42.000 --> 16:44.000
It is safe in my home.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.000
I must go away for a few days.

16:46.000 --> 16:49.000
Your friend, Diego Vega.

16:49.000 --> 16:53.000
Don Carlos receives the letter and says...

16:53.000 --> 16:55.000
What a generous invitation.

16:55.000 --> 16:57.000
Don Diego wants to protect Lolita.

16:57.000 --> 17:00.000
We must accept the invitation.

17:00.000 --> 17:02.000
Let us go immediately.

17:05.000 --> 17:07.000
Chapter 5.

17:07.000 --> 17:10.000
Lolita is in love.

17:10.000 --> 17:15.000
Don Diego's home in Reina de Los Angeles is big and beautiful.

17:15.000 --> 17:19.000
There are many rooms and many servants.

17:19.000 --> 17:23.000
There is a big garden with trees and flowers.

17:23.000 --> 17:26.000
Don Carlos and his family like it.

17:26.000 --> 17:32.000
Lolita, Mary Don Diego and this beautiful home is yours.

17:32.000 --> 17:34.000
She says Dona Catalina.

17:34.000 --> 17:36.000
I don't love Don Diego.

17:36.000 --> 17:38.000
I don't want to marry him.

17:38.000 --> 17:39.000
Says Lolita.

17:39.000 --> 17:44.000
Lolita, tonight your mother and I must visit our old friends.

17:44.000 --> 17:45.000
Says Don Carlos.

17:45.000 --> 17:47.000
Can you stay at home alone?

17:47.000 --> 17:49.000
Yes, of course.

17:49.000 --> 17:52.000
There are many books in Don Diego's library.

17:52.000 --> 17:55.000
I can stay here and read.

17:55.000 --> 17:57.000
Lolita looks at the books.

17:57.000 --> 17:59.000
How strange.

17:59.000 --> 18:00.000
She thinks.

18:00.000 --> 18:07.000
Don Diego has books about love, passion, adventure, horses and heroes.

18:07.000 --> 18:09.000
But he isn't strong.

18:09.000 --> 18:11.000
It is so lifeless.

18:11.000 --> 18:14.000
Suddenly there is a knock at the door.

18:14.000 --> 18:21.000
A servant opens it and Captain Ramon enters.

18:21.000 --> 18:25.000
He goes to the library and sees Lolita.

18:25.000 --> 18:27.000
I'm glad you are alone.

18:27.000 --> 18:30.000
You are a very beautiful girl.

18:30.000 --> 18:33.000
I have your father's permission to court you.

18:33.000 --> 18:39.000
I know that Don Diego wants to marry you, but I am superior in every way.

18:39.000 --> 18:41.000
Don Diego has no courage.

18:41.000 --> 18:43.000
He is a weak man.

18:43.000 --> 18:46.000
I am the captain of the Presidio.

18:46.000 --> 18:48.000
I am alone.

18:48.000 --> 18:49.000
Says Lolita.

18:49.000 --> 18:51.000
You cannot stay here.

18:51.000 --> 18:52.000
It is not right.

18:52.000 --> 18:54.000
Please go away.

18:54.000 --> 18:59.000
Captain Ramon takes her hand and says, don't run away, Lolita.

18:59.000 --> 19:01.000
You are mine.

19:01.000 --> 19:03.000
Kiss me.

19:03.000 --> 19:07.000
Lolita pushes him away and says, I don't want to kiss you.

19:07.000 --> 19:09.000
Go away.

19:09.000 --> 19:11.000
No, you are mine.

19:11.000 --> 19:13.000
You must marry me.

19:13.000 --> 19:16.000
Now kiss me.

19:16.000 --> 19:20.000
Lolita slaps the captain's face.

19:20.000 --> 19:27.000
At that moment, Zorro appears in the library and says, Captain Ramon, you are a villain.

19:27.000 --> 19:29.000
Don't touch Lolita.

19:29.000 --> 19:31.000
Leave this house immediately.

19:31.000 --> 19:35.000
I cannot forget this terrible insult.

19:35.000 --> 19:37.000
Says the captain.

19:37.000 --> 19:39.000
His face is red with anger.

19:39.000 --> 19:44.000
Zorro opens the door and kicks him out.

19:44.000 --> 19:47.000
Thank you for your help, Zorro.

19:47.000 --> 19:50.000
You are courageous and kind.

19:50.000 --> 19:52.000
I love you.

19:52.000 --> 19:58.000
Lolita says, Dear Lolita, I love you too, says Zorro.

19:58.000 --> 20:01.000
They embrace and kiss.

20:04.000 --> 20:06.000
Chapter 6.

20:06.000 --> 20:09.000
Friar Felipe.

20:09.000 --> 20:13.000
Captain Ramon returns to the Presidio.

20:13.000 --> 20:15.000
He is furious.

20:15.000 --> 20:21.000
I must punish Lolita, her family and Zorro for their insults.

20:21.000 --> 20:24.000
He thinks, I must write a letter to the governor.

20:24.000 --> 20:30.000
I must tell him that Don Carlos Pulido and his family are traitors.

20:30.000 --> 20:32.000
They are Zorro's friends.

20:32.000 --> 20:35.000
They help him.

20:35.000 --> 20:38.000
He writes the letter and sends it to the governor.

20:38.000 --> 20:44.000
He smiles and says, I want to see the Pulido family in prison.

20:44.000 --> 20:47.000
I want to see you in prison.

20:47.000 --> 20:49.000
Says a man's voice.

20:49.000 --> 20:53.000
Captain Ramon turns around and sees Zorro.

20:53.000 --> 20:55.000
You are a villain.

20:55.000 --> 20:58.000
Fight me, but don't hurt the Pulido family.

20:58.000 --> 21:00.000
Says Zorro.

21:00.000 --> 21:03.000
Sergeant Gonzalez, come quickly, says the captain.

21:03.000 --> 21:05.000
Zorro is here.

21:05.000 --> 21:07.000
Zorro disappears.

21:07.000 --> 21:09.000
I am here, Captain.

21:09.000 --> 21:11.000
Says Sergeant Gonzalez.

21:11.000 --> 21:14.000
Take all the soldiers and find Zorro.

21:14.000 --> 21:17.000
We must capture him.

21:17.000 --> 21:19.000
The soldiers follow Zorro.

21:19.000 --> 21:21.000
The night is dark.

21:21.000 --> 21:26.000
It is difficult to follow him because his horse is very fast.

21:26.000 --> 21:31.000
The next morning, the soldiers return to the Presidio.

21:31.000 --> 21:34.000
They are tired and angry.

21:34.000 --> 21:37.000
Zorro is still free.

21:37.000 --> 21:41.000
There are many people in front of the Presidio that morning.

21:41.000 --> 21:44.000
Don Diego is there too.

21:44.000 --> 21:47.000
Something is happening.

21:47.000 --> 21:52.000
An old friar is standing before the magistrate.

21:52.000 --> 21:58.000
The old friar is in chains.

21:58.000 --> 22:00.000
I am not a thief.

22:00.000 --> 22:01.000
Says the old friar.

22:01.000 --> 22:03.000
I am a poor friar.

22:03.000 --> 22:06.000
What is happening asks Don Diego.

22:06.000 --> 22:08.000
This old friar is a thief.

22:08.000 --> 22:10.000
He must be punished.

22:10.000 --> 22:12.000
Answers the magistrate.

22:12.000 --> 22:14.000
That is impossible.

22:14.000 --> 22:16.000
Friar Felipe is an honest man.

22:16.000 --> 22:18.000
I know him.

22:18.000 --> 22:20.000
Says Don Diego.

22:20.000 --> 22:22.000
No, you are wrong.

22:22.000 --> 22:24.000
Says the cruel magistrate.

22:24.000 --> 22:31.000
He calls two soldiers and says, whip this friar 15 times.

22:31.000 --> 22:34.000
The soldiers whip the old friar.

22:34.000 --> 22:37.000
And he falls to the ground.

22:37.000 --> 22:43.000
Don Diego is very angry because Friar Felipe is his friend.

22:43.000 --> 22:46.000
He returns to his father's hacienda.

22:46.000 --> 22:48.000
Good afternoon, my son.

22:48.000 --> 22:51.000
Says his father, Don Alejandro Vega.

22:51.000 --> 22:53.000
I am happy to see you.

22:53.000 --> 22:56.000
Come and tell me about Lolita.

22:56.000 --> 22:58.000
Does she want to marry you?

22:58.000 --> 23:02.000
I like Lolita, but she doesn't like me.

23:02.000 --> 23:04.000
She likes romantic men.

23:04.000 --> 23:05.000
What can I do?

23:05.000 --> 23:07.000
Ask Don Diego.

23:07.000 --> 23:10.000
Girls like courageous romantic men.

23:10.000 --> 23:12.000
You must talk about love.

23:12.000 --> 23:15.000
You must play the guitar and sing love songs.

23:15.000 --> 23:17.000
Give her some flowers.

23:17.000 --> 23:19.000
This is what young men do.

23:19.000 --> 23:21.000
Wake up, Diego.

23:21.000 --> 23:22.000
Says Don Alejandro.

23:22.000 --> 23:24.000
How ridiculous.

23:24.000 --> 23:26.000
I cannot do these stupid things.

23:26.000 --> 23:28.000
Says Don Diego.

23:28.000 --> 23:29.000
You must try.

23:29.000 --> 23:31.000
Lolita is a lovely girl.

23:31.000 --> 23:33.000
Says Don Alejandro.

23:33.000 --> 23:35.000
There are many problems in my life.

23:35.000 --> 23:37.000
I want to rest and meditate.

23:37.000 --> 23:39.000
Says Don Diego.

23:43.000 --> 23:45.000
Chapter 7.

23:45.000 --> 23:48.000
The Avengers.

23:48.000 --> 23:52.000
In the evening, the magistrate and his friends are in the tavern.

23:52.000 --> 23:55.000
They are laughing about the old friar.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.000
Why are you laughing?

23:58.000 --> 24:01.000
Ask some mysterious voice.

24:01.000 --> 24:05.000
They look at the door of the tavern and see Zorro.

24:05.000 --> 24:09.000
He has a pistol in one hand and a sword in the other.

24:09.000 --> 24:12.000
Magistrate, I'm here to punish you.

24:12.000 --> 24:14.000
Says Zorro.

24:14.000 --> 24:18.000
Old friar Felipe is not a thief and you know it.

24:18.000 --> 24:21.000
I am an important magistrate.

24:22.000 --> 24:24.000
I am an important magistrate.

24:24.000 --> 24:29.000
I don't like friars because they are your friends, Zorro.

24:29.000 --> 24:34.000
Zorro gives a whip to the magistrate's friend and says...

24:34.000 --> 24:38.000
Now whip this corrupt magistrate 15 times.

24:38.000 --> 24:40.000
But I cannot do this.

24:40.000 --> 24:41.000
Says the friend.

24:41.000 --> 24:43.000
Whip him or I whip you.

24:43.000 --> 24:44.000
Says Zorro.

24:44.000 --> 24:47.000
The friend whips the magistrate.

24:48.000 --> 24:52.000
After the punishment, the magistrate falls to the ground.

24:52.000 --> 24:55.000
This is how I punish dishonest people.

24:55.000 --> 24:57.000
Says Zorro.

24:57.000 --> 25:01.000
The next day, everyone talks about the magistrate's punishment.

25:01.000 --> 25:07.000
A group of young men want to help Captain Ramon arrest Zorro.

25:07.000 --> 25:11.000
They look for him in the hills and in the valleys.

25:11.000 --> 25:15.000
In the evening, they go to the Vega Hacienda.

25:15.000 --> 25:18.000
When Don Alejandro sees them, he says...

25:18.000 --> 25:20.000
Why are you all here?

25:20.000 --> 25:22.000
We are looking for Zorro.

25:22.000 --> 25:25.000
We want to capture the bandit and get the reward.

25:25.000 --> 25:27.000
But now we are tired and hungry.

25:27.000 --> 25:29.000
Can you give us some food?

25:29.000 --> 25:30.000
Yes, of course.

25:30.000 --> 25:31.000
Please come in.

25:31.000 --> 25:34.000
You can put your swords and pistols near the door.

25:34.000 --> 25:36.000
Says Don Alejandro.

25:36.000 --> 25:37.000
Sit down.

25:37.000 --> 25:40.000
Eat these cakes and drink this wine.

25:40.000 --> 25:44.000
Don Alejandro and Don Diego talk to the young men.

25:44.000 --> 25:47.000
At 9pm, Don Diego says...

25:47.000 --> 25:49.000
Please excuse me.

25:49.000 --> 25:52.000
I am tired and I am going to bed.

25:52.000 --> 25:53.000
Look, Diego.

25:53.000 --> 25:55.000
These young men are not tired.

25:55.000 --> 25:57.000
It's only 9pm.

25:57.000 --> 26:00.000
You are young, but you are always tired.

26:00.000 --> 26:02.000
Says Don Alejandro.

26:02.000 --> 26:04.000
Yes, Father.

26:04.000 --> 26:05.000
You are right.

26:05.000 --> 26:07.000
Good night, everyone.

26:07.000 --> 26:11.000
The others eat, drink, and sing.

26:12.000 --> 26:16.000
At midnight, a masked man appears at the door.

26:16.000 --> 26:19.000
Look, it is Zorro.

26:19.000 --> 26:21.000
Says one of the young men.

26:21.000 --> 26:22.000
Zorro the bandit.

26:22.000 --> 26:23.000
Zorro the bandit.

26:23.000 --> 26:25.000
They all say...

26:25.000 --> 26:29.000
Yes, I am Zorro, but I am not a bandit.

26:29.000 --> 26:32.000
I have principles and I fight for them.

26:32.000 --> 26:38.000
In California, we have corrupt political men, cruel magistrates, and dishonest people.

26:38.000 --> 26:40.000
I want to change this.

26:40.000 --> 26:44.000
I fight to help the poor, the natives, and the friars.

26:44.000 --> 26:46.000
What are your principles?

26:46.000 --> 26:48.000
We want to help the poor.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.000
The natives and the friars too.

26:50.000 --> 26:52.000
Says one young man.

26:52.000 --> 26:54.000
Our principles are the same.

26:54.000 --> 26:56.000
Says another.

26:56.000 --> 26:59.000
Come with me and we can fight together.

26:59.000 --> 27:02.000
We can make California a better place to live.

27:02.000 --> 27:03.000
Says Zorro.

27:03.000 --> 27:05.000
But who are you?

27:05.000 --> 27:06.000
Where do you live?

27:06.000 --> 27:08.000
Asks a young man.

27:08.000 --> 27:09.000
I can't tell you.

27:09.000 --> 27:10.000
It's a secret.

27:10.000 --> 27:11.000
Says Zorro.

27:11.000 --> 27:14.000
The young men talk together.

27:14.000 --> 27:17.000
Yes, we want to fight with you.

27:17.000 --> 27:19.000
We want justice in California.

27:19.000 --> 27:20.000
Our new name is...

27:20.000 --> 27:21.000
The Avengers.

27:21.000 --> 27:22.000
Says a young man.

27:22.000 --> 27:24.000
Yes, the Avengers.

27:24.000 --> 27:25.000
The Avengers.

27:25.000 --> 27:26.000
They all say...

27:26.000 --> 27:27.000
Good.

27:27.000 --> 27:29.000
We now fight together.

27:29.000 --> 27:30.000
Says Zorro.

27:30.000 --> 27:32.000
And leaves.

27:33.000 --> 27:35.000
California today.

27:35.000 --> 27:40.000
California is an important state of the United States.

27:40.000 --> 27:44.000
About 34 million people live there.

27:44.000 --> 27:49.000
Many old Spanish missions are now important cities and towns.

27:49.000 --> 27:53.000
Many people in California speak Spanish.

27:53.000 --> 28:00.000
Towns, streets, parks, schools, and other places often have Spanish names.

28:00.000 --> 28:04.000
The capital of California is Sacramento.

28:05.000 --> 28:08.000
California is famous for its natural beauty.

28:08.000 --> 28:17.000
There are tall mountains, green valleys, forests, sandy beaches, and hot deserts.

28:17.000 --> 28:31.000
Some beautiful national parks are Yosemite, Sequoia, Kings Canyon, Mirror Woods, Shasta, Death Valley, and Humbled Redwoods.

28:31.000 --> 28:36.000
Young people like Disneyland and the Great America theme park.

28:36.000 --> 28:40.000
Millions of tourists visit California every year.

28:40.000 --> 28:44.000
There are a lot of interesting places to visit.

28:44.000 --> 28:52.000
The University of California, Berkeley and Stanford University are two excellent universities.

28:52.000 --> 28:55.000
California is a cosmopolitan state.

28:55.000 --> 28:59.000
People from all over the world live there.

29:02.000 --> 29:06.000
Chapter 8. The Escape.

29:06.000 --> 29:09.000
The governor of California is here today.

29:09.000 --> 29:11.000
Says Sergeant Gonzales.

29:11.000 --> 29:14.000
Good, says Captain Ramon.

29:14.000 --> 29:16.000
I must speak to him.

29:16.000 --> 29:19.000
Good morning, Captain Ramon.

29:19.000 --> 29:20.000
Says the governor.

29:20.000 --> 29:22.000
I have your letter.

29:22.000 --> 29:26.000
Thank you for the information about the Pulido family.

29:26.000 --> 29:28.000
They are Zorro's friends.

29:28.000 --> 29:30.000
They are traitors.

29:30.000 --> 29:33.000
We must put them in prison and kill them.

29:33.000 --> 29:35.000
They are dangerous.

29:35.000 --> 29:37.000
What a good idea.

29:37.000 --> 29:42.000
My soldiers can arrest them today, says the captain.

29:42.000 --> 29:48.000
A group of soldiers goes to the Pulido Hacienda.

29:48.000 --> 29:53.000
They arrest Don Carlos, Dona Catalina, and Lolita.

29:53.000 --> 29:55.000
They take them to prison.

29:55.000 --> 29:58.000
Don Carlos is furious.

29:58.000 --> 30:01.000
His wife and daughter cry.

30:04.000 --> 30:08.000
When Don Diego hears about this, he goes to the governor.

30:08.000 --> 30:10.000
He asks him.

30:10.000 --> 30:13.000
Why is the Pulido family in prison?

30:13.000 --> 30:15.000
The governor answers.

30:15.000 --> 30:17.000
They are Zorro's friends.

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
They help and protect him.

30:19.000 --> 30:21.000
They are traitors.

30:21.000 --> 30:23.000
I cannot believe this.

30:23.000 --> 30:24.000
I know them.

30:24.000 --> 30:26.000
They are honest people.

30:26.000 --> 30:28.000
They don't help bandits.

30:28.000 --> 30:30.000
Says Don Diego.

30:30.000 --> 30:32.000
You are wrong, Don Diego.

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
They must be punished.

30:34.000 --> 30:37.000
The punishment for traitors is death.

30:37.000 --> 30:39.000
Says the governor.

30:39.000 --> 30:44.000
Early in the evening, Zorro sends a message to the Avengers.

30:44.000 --> 30:46.000
A message says.

30:46.000 --> 30:49.000
Meet me at midnight at the lake.

30:49.000 --> 30:51.000
Bring your swords and pistols.

30:51.000 --> 30:53.000
Pass the word to everyone.

30:53.000 --> 30:58.000
At midnight, Zorro and the Avengers meet at the lake.

30:58.000 --> 31:01.000
Every Avenger has a mask on his face.

31:01.000 --> 31:03.000
Zorro says.

31:03.000 --> 31:07.000
We are here to rescue Don Pulido and his family.

31:07.000 --> 31:09.000
They must escape from prison.

31:09.000 --> 31:11.000
They are innocent.

31:11.000 --> 31:13.000
We must be silent.

31:13.000 --> 31:15.000
Enter the prison and help them.

31:15.000 --> 31:19.000
Francisco, you take Don Carlos to the village of Pala.

31:19.000 --> 31:23.000
Jose, you take Dona Catalina to the Vega Hacienda.

31:23.000 --> 31:26.000
I want to take Lolita to Friar Felipe.

31:26.000 --> 31:29.000
They must hide for a few days.

31:29.000 --> 31:34.000
Zorro and the Avengers rescue the Pulido family.

31:34.000 --> 31:39.000
Don Carlos and Dona Catalina reach their destination.

31:39.000 --> 31:42.000
The soldiers follow Zorro and Lolita.

31:42.000 --> 31:46.000
Zorro's horse is very fast.

31:46.000 --> 31:51.000
Zorro and Lolita arrive at Friar Felipe's Hacienda.

31:51.000 --> 31:53.000
Zorro says.

31:53.000 --> 31:56.000
Can Lolita stay here with you for a few days?

31:56.000 --> 31:58.000
She is in danger.

31:58.000 --> 32:00.000
Yes, I can protect her.

32:00.000 --> 32:01.000
Says Friar Felipe.

32:01.000 --> 32:04.000
Zorro kisses Lolita and says.

32:04.000 --> 32:07.000
Always remember that I love you.

32:07.000 --> 32:11.000
Then he rides away on his horse.

32:11.000 --> 32:15.000
Chapter 9.

32:15.000 --> 32:19.000
The man behind the mask.

32:19.000 --> 32:22.000
The soldiers follow Zorro all night.

32:22.000 --> 32:25.000
They cannot capture him.

32:25.000 --> 32:31.000
The next night, Zorro silently enters the governor's home.

32:31.000 --> 32:35.000
He wants to talk to the governor and Captain Ramon.

32:35.000 --> 32:39.000
They are sitting near the fire.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.000
Zorro enters and says.

32:42.000 --> 32:45.000
Don't move and don't make a noise.

32:45.000 --> 32:47.000
I want to speak to you.

32:47.000 --> 32:51.000
He has a pistol in one hand and a sword in the other.

32:51.000 --> 32:54.000
Zorro, why are you here?

32:54.000 --> 32:56.000
Asks the governor.

32:56.000 --> 32:58.000
You are here to die.

32:58.000 --> 33:00.000
Says Captain Ramon.

33:00.000 --> 33:01.000
No.

33:01.000 --> 33:02.000
Answer Zorro.

33:02.000 --> 33:04.000
I am here to bring justice.

33:04.000 --> 33:06.000
I am here to learn the truth.

33:06.000 --> 33:09.000
Governor, you want to punch the Polito family.

33:09.000 --> 33:10.000
Why?

33:10.000 --> 33:12.000
They are traitors.

33:12.000 --> 33:14.000
They are your friends, Zorro.

33:14.000 --> 33:15.000
They help you.

33:15.000 --> 33:17.000
Your friends are my enemies.

33:17.000 --> 33:19.000
Says the governor.

33:19.000 --> 33:20.000
They are not traitors.

33:20.000 --> 33:22.000
They do not help me.

33:22.000 --> 33:24.000
They are not my friends.

33:24.000 --> 33:25.000
He says.

33:25.000 --> 33:27.000
Look at this letter.

33:27.000 --> 33:28.000
It accuses them.

33:28.000 --> 33:30.000
Says the governor.

33:30.000 --> 33:33.000
Zorro reads the letter and says.

33:33.000 --> 33:35.000
It is Captain Ramon's letter.

33:35.000 --> 33:37.000
He accuses the Polito family.

33:37.000 --> 33:40.000
Zorro looks at the captain and says.

33:40.000 --> 33:45.000
Captain, you are a liar, but I am here to punish you.

33:45.000 --> 33:48.000
Tell the governor the truth about the Polito family.

33:48.000 --> 33:54.000
Zorro puts his pistol to Captain Ramon's head and says.

33:54.000 --> 33:57.000
Tell the governor the truth or I shoot.

33:57.000 --> 34:00.000
Captain Ramon is silent.

34:00.000 --> 34:02.000
His face is white.

34:02.000 --> 34:04.000
The truth, you liar.

34:04.000 --> 34:05.000
Says Zorro.

34:05.000 --> 34:08.000
Yes, I am a liar.

34:08.000 --> 34:11.000
The letter is not true.

34:11.000 --> 34:13.000
This is terrible.

34:13.000 --> 34:14.000
Says the governor.

34:14.000 --> 34:16.000
You are a liar.

34:16.000 --> 34:19.000
You cannot be the captain of the Presidio.

34:19.000 --> 34:23.000
At that moment, the captain pulls out his sword.

34:23.000 --> 34:25.000
He begins to fight Zorro.

34:25.000 --> 34:27.000
It is a long sword fight.

34:27.000 --> 34:31.000
In the end, Zorro kills Captain Ramon.

34:32.000 --> 34:34.000
The captain is dead.

34:34.000 --> 34:36.000
Says Zorro to the governor.

34:36.000 --> 34:40.000
Outside the governor's home, there are many soldiers.

34:40.000 --> 34:42.000
They want to capture Zorro.

34:42.000 --> 34:45.000
He sees Lolita on her horse.

34:45.000 --> 34:47.000
He shouts.

34:47.000 --> 34:50.000
Lolita, come with me.

34:50.000 --> 34:52.000
We must hide in the old tavern.

34:52.000 --> 34:55.000
This time it is very difficult to escape.

34:55.000 --> 34:57.000
There are soldiers all around us.

34:57.000 --> 34:59.000
I'm happy to be with you, Zorro.

34:59.000 --> 35:00.000
Says Lolita.

35:00.000 --> 35:02.000
I'm not scared.

35:02.000 --> 35:06.000
Zorro and Lolita hide inside the old tavern.

35:06.000 --> 35:08.000
The soldiers try to enter.

35:08.000 --> 35:11.000
Zorro is ready to fight.

35:11.000 --> 35:15.000
Suddenly, the Avengers come to rescue Zorro and Lolita.

35:15.000 --> 35:18.000
They explain many things to the governor.

35:18.000 --> 35:21.000
The governor pardons Zorro.

35:21.000 --> 35:24.000
Zorro and Lolita will be ready.

35:24.000 --> 35:25.000
Zorro.

35:25.000 --> 35:29.000
Zorro and Lolita walk out of the old tavern.

35:29.000 --> 35:31.000
They are free.

35:31.000 --> 35:33.000
Everyone is happy and cheers.

35:33.000 --> 35:34.000
Yeah!

35:34.000 --> 35:35.000
Yeah!

35:35.000 --> 35:36.000
Zorro!

35:36.000 --> 35:37.000
Zorro!

35:37.000 --> 35:38.000
The governor says,

35:38.000 --> 35:41.000
Now that you are free, show us your face.

35:41.000 --> 35:42.000
Yes!

35:42.000 --> 35:43.000
Yes!

35:43.000 --> 35:44.000
Yes!

35:44.000 --> 35:45.000
Show us!

35:45.000 --> 35:50.000
The people say, Zorro takes off his black mask.

35:50.000 --> 35:52.000
It's Don Diego Vega!

35:52.000 --> 35:54.000
Exclaimed Sergeant Gonzales.

35:54.000 --> 35:57.000
Everyone is very surprised.

35:57.000 --> 36:00.000
My son, Don Diego, I can't believe it!

36:00.000 --> 36:02.000
Exclaimed Don Alejandro.

36:02.000 --> 36:05.000
Lolita looks at him and says,

36:05.000 --> 36:06.000
Is this true?

36:06.000 --> 36:08.000
Or is it a dream?

36:08.000 --> 36:10.000
Are you really Don Diego?

36:10.000 --> 36:12.000
Yes, my love.

36:12.000 --> 36:15.000
I am your Don Diego and your Zorro.

36:15.000 --> 36:18.000
He says, Embracing Lolita.

